@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@
+# Sprint 72B — Public Conversation Product Layer
+
+Sprint 72B builds the public product layer on top of the plugin-based runtime introduced in Sprint 72A.
+
+## Goal
+
+Separate public conversation, visible actions and observable process views from the technical plugin/runtime trace.
+
+This sprint is not a cosmetic UI pass. It defines the boundary between:
+
+- client-facing conversation;
+- public process explanation;
+- summarized diagnostic view;
+- developer trace;
+- plugin-declared actions;
+- blocked capability claims.
+
+## Delivered
+
+- Added `aca_os.public_conversation_product_layer`.
+- Added public projection from developer trace into `public_process_view` and `diagnostic_view`.
+- Added claim filtering for blocked capabilities such as real claim lookup, real document upload and real representative transfer.
+- Added capability-derived visible actions.
+- Added public action capabilities to the bundled plugins.
+- Added Studio markers and endpoint contract wiring for the public layer.
+- Added Sprint 72B tests for trace separation, action derivation, blocked claims and generic plugin fallback.
+
+## Architectural rules
+
+- Public UI never consumes `developer_trace` directly.
+- Developer trace is transformed into public views before display.
+- Visible actions are derived from plugin capabilities.
+- Public responses must not claim capabilities that the active plugin blocks or does not declare.
+- `generic.open_chat` remains the neutral fallback when no business plugin is installed.
+
+## Validation
+
+```bash
+py -m pytest -q tests/test_public_conversation_product_layer.py
+py -m pytest -q
+```
